    • saveUsingRepository

      @PostMapping("/processoperation") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<com.bmr.BMR_Generator.dto.ProcessOperationDTO> saveUsingRepository(@RequestBody com.bmr.BMR_Generator.entity.ProcessOperation processOperation)
      Saves the provided ProcessOperation. If the opNumber of the ProcessOperation is 0, it assigns a new sequential value based on the maximum opNumber found in the database.

      This method delegates the actual saving operation to the service layer. If an error occurs during the saving process, it is handled by the global exception handler GlobalExceptionHandler.

      Parameters:
      processOperation - The ProcessOperation entity to be saved.
      Returns:
      A ProcessOperationDTO representing the saved ProcessOperation.
      Throws:
      com.bmr.BMR_Generator.rest.response.BrApiServerException - If an error occurs during the saving process.
      com.bmr.BMR_Generator.rest.response.NotAllowedRequestParameters - } If the request parameters are not allowed.
